Build F3 (20020612)
Win2k

Set the tracker rectangle to (0, 0, 0, 0) and call open().
You get the following walkback:

java.lang.ArithmeticException: / by zero
	at org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Tracker.computeProportions(Tracker.java:282)
	at org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Tracker.setRectangles(Tracker.java:682)
	at org.eclipse.swt.guibuilder.Example.main(Example.java:17)
Exception in thread "main" 

Here's an example to see this:

public static void main(String[] args) {
	Display display = new Display();
	Shell shell = new Shell(display);

	Tracker tracker = new Tracker (display, SWT.NONE);

	Rectangle[] array = new Rectangle[1];
	array[0] = new Rectangle(0, 0, 0, 0);
	tracker.setRectangles(array);

	shell.open();
	tracker.open();

	while (!shell.isDisposed())
		if (!display.readAndDispatch())
			display.sleep();
}
